  "narrative": {
    "intro": "NAICS 336411 obligations for FY2026 to date total $31.6B across 4,113 awards, with an average award size of $7.7M and year-over-year change down 48.4%. Obligations for FY26 to date are lower than the FY25 total of $61.2B and follow a multi-year pattern that included $60.1B in FY23 and $44.2B in FY24. The Department of Defense accounts for the vast majority of FY2026 to date obligations at $31.1B, while other federal buyers total far smaller amounts, led by the Department of Homeland Security at $131M and the Department of Commerce at $108M. At the vendor level, LOCKHEED MARTIN CORPORATION leads vendors at $8.1B followed by multiple entries from THE BOEING COMPANY totaling $5.8B, $3B, $2.4B, $1.6B, and $1.1B in separate listings. Other notable vendors include SIKORSKY AIRCRAFT CORPORATION at $2.1B, BELL TEXTRON INC at $1.5B, SIERRA NEVADA COMPANY, LLC at $1.4B, and RTX CORPORATION at $557M. FY2026 to date figures are partial fiscal year totals.",
